# Supporting — Figma URL routing

When the user's message contains a `figma.com/(design|board|make|proto|file)/...` URL, do NOT manually fetch the design. Instead, route to the right command:

| User intent                                              | Command                                       |
| -------------------------------------------------------- | --------------------------------------------- |
| Build NEW components / icons / tokens                    | `/figma-build <url> [layerHint]`              |
| UPDATE existing components / icons / tokens              | `/figma-update <url>`                         |
| Icons only                                                | `/figma-icons <url>`                          |
| Tokens only                                               | `/figma-tokens <url>`                         |

All routes spawn the same coordinator (`.cursor/prompts/figma-coordinator.md`). Don't call individual specialists (`figma-fetcher`, `component-builder`, etc.) directly — the coordinator orchestrates them with proper slicing.

If the user's intent is ambiguous, ask ONE focused question (build vs update? full vs icons vs tokens?) before running anything.
